,Recommended,589760,31745646,Posted: 14 May,all,Homiccus,"A good game for all motoring enthusiasts. Has its quirks and is full of glitches, but on a good path.In Revhead you control an amateur racing driver trying to make his way up the local ladder. The game is divided into three distinctive parts: garage, racing tracks and the town, each with set of activities.Without further ado:The Likes.- genuine feel of backwater, dilapidated garage that sees old jalopys and bangers more often than flashy supercars.- every car comprises dozens of parts which are removable, configurable and swappable. Need wider tyres? No problem, buy or scavenge a set of rims and off you go. Engine too small? Get a used V8 from an old 4x4 and stick it in. Change the drivetrain to awd while you're at it aswell. Yup. That's how far this game goes in ride customization.- parts and cars market is accessed through ads section in a newspaper. That's right. No PC or iPad for you. To find what you want you need to scour the ads and hope for the best. I love this, it adds a lot to the flavour.- driving and racing. At first I shared the view of many reviewers here on steam, that the car driving is unplayable. And then I realised that I'm trying to drive a 20 year old car with 300k on the clock and worn out tyres at 60mph and expect it to corner like a beemer. Ain't gonna happen mate. Change suspension. Install stiffer sway bars. Change tyres. Fix steering. Bam. Car handles like a dream. Even on a keyboard. Stop whining and git gud.- impromptu drag races in the town add to the range of activities. They're a good source of money and are done onthe main town map. Nice touch.The dislikes- genuine feel of an indie game made on a shoestring budget. Requires tons of polish to shine.- the graphics looks a bit dated for 2017. Cars look unrealistic - we need more dirt! - and are not tremendously detailed.- the Aussie setting is a bit cheesy and over the top. The game tries to be more Australian than Australians.- the town feels dead and needs more day-to-day traffic and pedestrians.- last but not least: Revhead desperately needs more content. More cars, more tracks, more engines, more parts.Overall, I'd give the game 6.5/10 at the current stage of development. Solid game but requires a lot of tlc to shine."
